modules.description: Provides functions to retrieve the keyboard height, register event listeners for specific events, and handle lifecycle events such as showing or hiding. Operates on a private type representing event data, typically used in JavaScript interop contexts. Used to manage UI interactions and respond to system events like keyboard appearance or view transitions.
Handles keyboard show/hide events and adjusts the viewport accordingly. Works with native keyboard events and DOM elements. Adjusts layout when the hardware keyboard is displayed on mobile devices.

Manages system events like keyboard appearance and view transitions through event data handling. Supports retrieving keyboard height and registering listeners for specific actions. Operates on a private event type, enabling UI adjustments based on dynamic changes. Examples include updating layout when the keyboard appears or logging event triggers during app lifecycle changes.
